# üêû bug report

### Description

I'm running into some strange behavior on Angular 9.1.11. I have a simple app that only uses the app.component.ts. A public class var (boolean) controls whether a button in the template is disabled or not.

Change Detection (using `changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.Default`) is working absolutely fine in the dev build, but it **does NOT work in the prod build** of the app.

I have to import and inject `ChangeDetectorRef` into the `AppComponent` class and manually trigger the `.detectChanges() ` method to make it work in the prod build (all of this works automatically in the dev build).

Any suggestions what may be causing the behavior in the prod build ?


